# 🌿 TouchGrass

A lightweight cross-platform python productivity timer that reminds you to take a break.

---

## ✨ Features

- ⏱️ Customizable work session duration
- 🔔 Desktop notifications via `plyer` (works on Ubuntu/Linux,macOS,Windows)
- 🔊 Audio alert when your session ends
- ⚙️ JSON-based settings for easy configuration
- 🧩 Modular codebase — notification and time logic are decoupled

---

## 🖥️ Tested On

- Ubuntu 22.04 / 24.04 (Linux)
- Windows 10/11
- Python 3.7+

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/bAmeGR/TouchGrass.git
cd TouchGrass
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Run the app

```bash
python main.py
```

---

## ⚙️ Configuration

Edit `settings.json` to customize default session durations and notification preferences:

```json
{
  "default_duration_minutes": 25,
  "notification_title": "Time to TouchGrass!",
  "notification_message": "Step away from the screen and take a break."
}
```

---

## 📦 Requirements

```
plyer
```

Install with:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## 💡 Why I Built This

Extended screen time without breaks is a real productivity and health issue.            TouchGrass is a minimal
no-distraction tool that runs quietly in the background and nudges you to step away no accounts no login no cloud no bloat.

